Towers of Hanoi

This program solves the Towers of Hanoi puzzle.

Input: Number of disks initially on the source pin
Output: Number of time the function towers is activated. 

To compile:

g++ towers-of-hanoi.cxx

Try to figure of out how many time towers( ) is activated when the number
of disks is 64.

Ans: 2^(64) - 1. Thank you Professor Micheal

Warning: Don't run the program for 64 disks.

